headlines.description: — Kevin Durant's tiebreaker jumper was like so many before — right on target in the closing seconds.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant tiebreaker lifts Suns over Mavs in showcase of stars

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton scored 29 points, including a 3-pointer with 2.7 seconds left, to give the Indiana Pacers a 125-122 victory Sunday over the Chicago Bulls.

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Anthony Davis is showing he is ready to shoulder the load for the Los Angeles Lakers with LeBron James out of the lineup.
headlines.shortLinkText: Davis leads Lakers past Warriors 113-105 in Curry's return

headlines.description: — Mikal Bridges went 9 for 9 in a 19-point first quarter, finishing with 33 to lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 102-86 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday night. Two nights after coming from 28 down to beat Boston in the biggest comeback in the...
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges' perfect 1st quarter sends Nets past Hornets, 102-86

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored eight of his 41 points from the foul line in the final three minutes Sunday night to the lead the Portland Trail Blazers to a 122-119 win over the Orlando Magic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 41, Blazers hold off Magic 122-119

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 31 points and the Houston Rockets got a 142-110 victory over San Antonio on Sunday, beating the Spurs for the second straight night in a matchup of the Western Conference’s worst teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green has 31, Rockets beat Spurs again with 142-110 rout

events.name: Utah Jazz at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 38 points and seven rebounds in his return from a five-game absence and the Oklahoma City Thunder led all the way while beating the Utah Jazz 129-119 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander returns with 38 as Thunder beat Jazz

events.name: New York Knicks at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored a career-high 38 points, playing 55 minutes in place of injured starter Jalen Brunson, and the New York Knicks outlasted the Boston Celtics 131-129 in two overtimes Sunday night for their season-high ninth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley scores 38 in start, Knicks outlast Celtics in 2 OTs

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 23 points, had a season-high 13 assists and rebounded his intentionally missed shot with a second left for his fourth-triple double of the season as...
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis triple-double helps Bucks outlast Wizards 117-111

headlines.description: — It had been a rough week for the Los Angeles Clippers. A five-game losing streak. The team plane got struck by lightning. They gave up 51 points in the third quarter against Memphis.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Leonard big in 4Q, Clippers beat Grizzlies 135-129
